  "prompt": "Why does Enrique Iglesias always wear a cap when performing?",
  "response": "Enrique Iglesias is known for frequently wearing a cap during his performances and public appearances. While he has not explicitly stated a singular reason, it is widely believed that he wears a cap for multiple reasons:\n\n1. **Comfort and Style:** The cap has become a trademark of his casual, laid-back style. It fits his personal brand and image that his fans have come to recognize and love.\n\n2. **Practicality:** Performing under stage lights can be very hot and wearing a cap may provide some comfort and shade from the intense lighting.\n\n3. **Confidence:** There have been speculations that Enrique may wear a cap to cover a scar on his head resulting from an accident involving a drone during a concert in 2015. However, this is just one of the many theories.\n\n4. **Consistency:** Artists often maintain certain stylistic choices to create a consistent and recognizable look. By always wearing a cap, Enrique maintains a signature look that fans can easily associate with him.\n\nUltimately, whether it\u2019s for fashion, comfort, or personal preference, his choice to wear a cap has become an iconic part of his persona as a performer.",
